// Airbnb JavaScript Style Guide — `no-implied-eval`: never pass a string to a
// timer; it is evaluated like `eval`. Flags `setTimeout`/`setInterval` whose
// FIRST argument is a string literal (`setTimeout("doStuff()", 100)`). This is a
// syntactic subset of ESLint's rule (string-literal first arg only, no taint
// tracking). A function first argument — arrow, function expression, or a bare
// identifier reference — is the correct form and stays silent.
language js

or {
  `setTimeout($first, $...)`,
  `setInterval($first, $...)`
} as $call where {
  $first <: string(),
  register_diagnostic(span=$call, message="Do not pass a string to `setTimeout`/`setInterval` (implied eval); pass a function instead.", severity="error")
}
